<HEADLINE>
<P>
CATHOLIC LEAGUE REBUTTAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 You printed a letter (Nov. 20, TV Times) from the Catholic League, which 
attempted to whitewash the history of Catholic destruction of American Indian 
culture. The writer asked you why your author (Wounded Knee -- "Survival of the 
Spirit") didn't portray the good side of Christian-Indian interaction, and 
whether blacks and Jews are exempt from criticism. 
</P>
<P>
 The answer is that blacks and Jews did not have a program of slavery, cultural 
genocide, murder, forced religious conversion and violent parochial school 
indoctrination of Indians -- white Christians did, and in much of the world 
today, they still do. 
</P>
<P>
 Jack L. Schwartz, Los Angeles (former staff attorney, American Indian Movement 
in Wounded Knee, S.D.) 
</P>
</TEXT>
