<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA120494-0076 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 104689 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
December 4, 1994, Sunday, Bulldog Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part A; Page 33; Column 5; National Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
32 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
GREECE ON WATCH LIST OVER PIRACY OF MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Clinton Administration elevated Greece to its priority watch list that 
could lead to sanctions for the government's alleged failure to protect U.S. 
movies and recordings from piracy. 
</P>
