<TEXT>
<P>
 Festivals, Feasts & Fairs 
</P>
<P>
 VENTURA -- If you're in search of seasonal fun today, drive north for 
Ventura's 18th annual Holiday Street Fair, 11 a.m.-4 p.m. on Main Street. 
Featured: More than 500 artisans, kids' activities, food and entertainment. 
Free.Mark your calendars for the 18th annual Parade of Lights in Ventura Harbor 
on Dec. 17. This year's parade, themed "Country Western Christmas," starts at 6 
p.m. (805) 648-2075. 
</P>
<P>
 PETALUMA -- A Los Posadas procession, carolers, dancers and early California 
foods are highlights at the Adobe Luminaria Fiesta, 2 p.m. Dec. 10. The free 
event concludes with the lighting of 1,000 luminaria at dusk. At the Petaluma 
Adobe State Historic Park, 3325 Adobe Road. The Holiday Lighted Boat Parade 
glides into the downtown harbor at 6:30 p.m. Dec. 10. (707) 769-0429. 
</P>
<P>
 JAMESTOWN -- Ride the rails with the Big Man in the red suit on one of 
Railtown's Santa Trains. Train rides with Santa Claus through the Gold Country 
are offered on Dec. 10, 11 and 18. Departures are at 10:30 a.m., noon, 1:30 and 
3 p.m. from Railtown, Fifth Avenue at Reservoir Road. $8, general; $4, kids 
3-12. For reservations, call (209) 984-3953. 
</P>
<P>
 FERNDALE -- A holiday procession is in store at the Ferndale Christmas Lighted 
Tractor Parade, 7 p.m. Dec. 17 along Main Street. (707) 786-4477. 
</P>
<P>
 SAN LUIS OBISPO -- Decemberfest brings a sparkling line-up of holiday music, 
dance, exhibits and activities to venues all over the city, Dec. 8-11. Among 
the offerings is Street Fest, 11 a.m.-4 p.m. Dec. 10 on Garden Street. A 
Victorian tea, a presentation of "How the Grinch Stole Christmas," a cookie 
bazaar and many other events are planned. For a complete schedule, call (805) 
541-0286.  
</P>
<P>
 Call listed phone numbers for directions. MARY FRANCES SMITH 
