<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEAL OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lake Arrowhead Resort is offering a $149 midweek Snow Valley ski package for 
two through March 31, 1995. The price, which is good Sunday through Thursday 
and is based on availability and double occupancy, includes one night's 
accommodation at the 261-room resort (usually $99-$199); two lift tickets for 
Snow Valley (usually $39 per person); ski, boots and pole rentals ($16 per 
person -- package rate does not change if rentals are not included); two 
90-minute ski lessons ($19 per person), and a full breakfast (about $10 per 
person). The price includes taxes but not transportation to Snow Valley. Also 
available: weekend packages and cross-country ski packages. For information and 
reservations, call (800) 800-6792. Free for the Asking 
</P>
<P>
 A new brochure from the American Automobile Assn. may help temper some of your 
fears about sending your child off alone on an airplane. "Flying Alone: Handy 
Advice for Kids Traveling Solo" offers suggestions on making reservations, 
packing, dressing; covers some of the safeguards that airlines use to make sure 
that little travelers arrive when and where they are supposed to, and includes 
a checklist for parents. "Flying Alone" is available at many AAA offices by 
sending a stamped, self-addressed business-sized envelope to: Flying Alone, 
Mail Stop 800, 1000 AAA Drive, Heathrow, Fla. 32746. This Week's Holidays 
</P>
<P>
 Banking and government offices will be closed or services curtailed in the 
following countries and their dependencies this week because of national and 
religious holidays: 
</P>
<P>
 Week of Dec. 5 
</P>
<P>
 Monday: Haiti, Thailand, Tonga 
</P>
<P>
 Tuesday: Finland, Ivory Coast Rep., Spain 
</P>
<P>
 Wednesday: Cuba, Italy, Ivory Coast Rep. 
</P>
<P>
