<P>
NCAA VOLLEYBALL; BRUINS, TROJANS WIN AT HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The UCLA and USC women's volleyball teams each won home matches Saturday in 
the second round of the NCAA tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 3 UCLA used a balanced attack to defeat Georgia Tech, 15-7, 15-9, 15-8, at 
Pauley Pavilion. 
</P>
<P>
 Freshman Kara Milling led the Bruins (29-3) with 12 kills. Annett Buckner and 
Jenny Johnson each contributed 11. 
</P>
<P>
 Kim Krull twisted her ankle on the first play of the game but returned to add 
10 kills against Georgia Tech (26-9). 
</P>
<P>
 No. 9 USC defeated No. 19 New Mexico, 15-13, 15-4, 15-6, behind a powerful 
performance by Meika Wagner at the Lyon Center. Wagner had 17 kills and hit 
.538 for the Trojans (21-7). Lauri Yust and Kelly Kuebler contributed 16 and 11 
kills, respectively. 
