<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL VOLLEYBALL STATE CHAMPIONSHIPS; NEWPORT HARBOR SWEEPS TO TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Misty May had 21 kills to lead Newport Harbor to a 15-4, 16-14, 15-10 victory 
over Stockton St. Mary's in the girls' volleyball State Division I championship 
match Saturday at Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 May, a 5-9 senior who has orally committed to Long Beach State, also had 10 
digs for Newport Harbor (33-1), ranked No. 1 in the nation by polls in USA 
Today and Volleyball Monthly. 
</P>
<P>
 Jen Canevari had 15 kills for St. Mary's (35-5). 
</P>
<P>
 In Division II, Megan O'Brien had 21 kills to lead Mountain View St. Francis 
(38-3) to its second State title with a 10-15, 15-9, 15-11, 15-11 victory over 
Huntington Beach (19-4), led by Melissa Wendt with 23 kills. 
</P>
<P>
 In Division III, San Jose Archbishop Mitty won its second consecutive title by 
defeating Bakersfield Centennial, 15-11, 15-8, 15-0. 
</P>
<P>
 In Division IV, Santa Ana Calvary Chapel defeated Orinda Miramonte, 15-6, 
15-5, 15-2. Courtney Owens had 15 kills for the Eagles (20-4). Miramonte ends 
22-5. 
</P>
<P>
 In Division V, Brentwood won its second consecutive State title, defeating 
Oakland College Prep, 15-8, 15-5, 16-14. Erin Hawkins had 10 kills for 
Brentwood (30-1). MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
