<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL 1994-1995 / SMALL SCHOOLS; EXPRESS LEAGUE--HERITAGE CHRISTIAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL: 13-7 LEAGUE: 11-3 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: RECORD AT SCHOOL Bob Williams: 0-0 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS 
YR. HGT. P David Acheson Jr. 5-11 G Jay Williams Jr. 5-11 G 04,16,05,06,04 TOP 
RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Robert Bozarth Jr. 5-11 G Chris Campbell Jr. 6-0 F Kevin 
Coke Jr. 6-2 F 04,19,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P Dan Dressendorfer Fr. 
5-11 G Jim Findlater So. 6-4 C OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Heritage Christian lost a gem in Steve Acheson, but have two new ones in David 
Acheson and Williams. Williams averaged 15 points last season and David Acheson 
14, but they will have to increase their output to get the Patriots some extra 
victories. Heritage Christian got second-place last year, but Williams hopes 
his team will do one better in his first year coaching the Patriots. In 
addition to the two scorers, Heritage Christian's strength lies in its speed 
and quickness, along with its outside shooting. The Patriots play a running 
style and scoring 100 points a game is a realistic goal. Williams is concerned 
about height, but with Findlater and Coke, the Patriots should be bigger than 
most teams in the small Express League. 
</P>
