league's most valuable player after averaging 22 points. He has already 
committed to the University of San Francisco. Masters and Baker are another 
pair of all-league seniors who averaged just over 10 points. Masters was the 
Tartans starting quarterback and is an excellent all-around athlete. Larson 
bypassed the junior varsity team and has proved to be a legitimate young 
talent. Ohara, in his first year after taking over for Rick Bauer who switched 
to Dana Hills, said he wants the Tartans to again challenge for the Division 
V-AA title and improve on their record from last season. The Tartan's best 
assets are their experience, quickness and athletic ability. Their weaknesses 
lie in rebounding and defensive transition, Ohara said. 
</P>
<P>
 SCHEDULE 
</P>
