<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; LOS ALAMITOS TOUGH INSIDE, WINS TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cory Johnson scored 22 points to lead Los Alamitos to a 72-53 victory over 
Corona del Mar in the championship game of the Daily Pilot Tip-Off Classic at 
Corona del Mar High. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnson made two three-pointers and eight of 10 free throws for the Griffins 
(4-0). He also had five rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 But the key for Los Alamitos was its dominance inside. A.D. Lamoreux and 
Jeremy Vandervoet controlled the lane, scoring 15 points each. They combined 
for 14 rebounds, and Vandervoet blocked six shots. 
</P>
<P>
 "They (Lamoreux and Vandervoet) were able to do the job inside," Griffins 
Coach Steve Brooks said. "We've got some things to work on, but I'm pleased 
with where we are at this point." 
</P>
<P>
 The Sea Kings (3-1) were led by Brian Fracalosy's 12 points but never made a 
serious run. The Griffins took an early 14-2 lead in the first quarter, and 
Corona del Mar didn't get closer than nine points after that. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sea Kings trailed, 47-37, at the end of three quarters and Los Alamitos 
went on a 14-8 run in the first four minutes of the fourth quarter to put the 
game out of reach. 
</P>
<P>
 In the third-place game: 
</P>
<P>
 Estancia 57, Newport Harbor 37 -- Zack Richardson had 14 points and Bryan 
Byrne added 12 for Estancia (3-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the final of the Mission Viejo Diablo Inferno tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Viejo 77, Cypress 73 -- Tyler Kalklosch hit a 55-footer with 1.9 
seconds left in regulation, and the Diablos then outscored Cypress 11-7 in the 
overtime. Kalklosch had 18 points and Austin Moherman 16 to lead Mission Viejo 
(3-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the final of the National Sports Grill tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Servite 62, Woodbridge 42 -- Mark Seaton had 28 points and 12 rebounds and 
David Downs had 17 points and eight rebounds for Servite (4-0). Seaton and 
Downs were co-most valuable players. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Burgess had 14 points for Woodbridge (3-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the final of the Orange Lutheran tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 61, Magnolia 46 -- Most valuable player Danny Garcia scored 18 points, 
and Andy Lauridsen added 16 for Orange (4-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the third-place game: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran 46, Saddleback 44 -- Sonny Madsen and Brian Sappington had 
eight points to lead Orange Lutheran (2-1), which outscored Saddleback 17-15 in 
the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 In the final of the San Luis Obispo tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita 69, San Luis Obispo 61 -- Allen Krist scored 28 points and 
grabbed 12 rebounds as the Eagles outscored San Luis Obispo, 14-4, after 
trailing by one at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 Tournament most valuable player Dennis Keane added 16 points, and Brendan 
Mulligan had 12 for Santa Margarita (3-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the final of the Buena Park tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel 66, Garden Grove 61 -- Isaac Leasau was named tournament Most 
Valuable Player and freshman Joe Ortiz and Kevin Falconer were named 
all-tournament selections for Calvary Chapel. Mike Campuzano scored 24 points 
for Garden Grove (3-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the final of the Brea-Olinda tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Katella 69, El Dorado 60 -- Mike Pahl scored 20 points and Carlos Romero 19 to 
lead Katella, which led, 37-31, at the half. 
</P>
<P>
 In a consolation game: 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza 70, Brea 65 -- Josh Greer had a game-high 19 points to lead 
Esperanza (3-1). 
</P>
