<HEADLINE>
<P>
WRESTLING / STATE JC MEET; MOORPARK'S JIMENEZ 4TH IN HIS CLASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRYAN RODGERS, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Moorpark College wrestling team's season ended on a disappointing note 
when John Jimenez and Tim Bonebright were defeated in semifinal matches of the 
state wrestling tournament at Rio Hondo College on Saturday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 Jimenez, who competes in the 134-pound class, and Bonebright (142 pounds) were 
the top finishers for Moorpark, which qualified 10 wrestlers for the 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Jimenez (28-12) lost to Cerritos' David Gayer, 3-2, in an aggressive match. 
Several times the referee warned the wrestlers that they could be disqualified 
jostling after the whistle. 
</P>
<P>
 The bout was delayed 10 minutes when Jimenez suffered a cut to the left side 
of his nose. 
</P>
<P>
 Jimenez lost to Shane Holloway of Rancho Santiago, 9-1, in the consolation 
round to place fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 Bonebright lost to Eddie Ramos of Fresno City College, 11-4, in the 
semifinals. Ramos was seeded No. 1 in the class and is the defending state 
champion. 
</P>
<P>
 "Tim went up against the top opponent in the state," Moorpark Coach John 
Keever said. "I know that he did everything he could." 
</P>
<P>
 Bonebright lost to Juan Alvarez from Cerritos College, 6-5, in the fifth-place 
match. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark's Kyle Plummer (158) defeated Diablo Valley's Josh Nagar, 4-0, in the 
fifth-place match. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark's Jeremy Pratt (167) finished eighth after forfeiting his final match 
because of a shoulder injury. 
</P>
</TEXT>
