<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL / MOORPARK TOURNAMENT; VENTURA WORKS OVERTIME TO BEAT 
MOORPARK FOR TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RON STAPP, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Freshman guard Rafer Alston scored seven of his 16 points in overtime Saturday 
night to lead Ventura College to an 82-75 victory over Moorpark in the 
championship game of the Moorpark tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Alston made five of six free throws, the last giving his team an 80-73 lead 
with 19 seconds to play in the extra period. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark (6-3) led most of the game. The Raiders opened a 47-37 lead when 
Jaime Jaquez scored on a layup three minutes into the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 But Ventura (9-0) stayed close behind a tough full-court defense, which led to 
numerous baskets off Moorpark turnovers. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura finally took the lead, 66-65, when Curtis Gaines, the tournament's 
most valuable player, scored inside with 1 minute 30 seconds left in 
regulation. Alston followed with a jump shot to give Ventura a three-point lead 
with 35 seconds to play. 
</P>
<P>
 But Moorpark forward David Fennell, who scored 14 points, made his fourth 
three-point basket to tie the score, 68-68, with 20 seconds to play.  
</P>
<P>
 Both teams had a chance to win in regulation, but missed last-second shots. 
</P>
<P>
 Jaquez led all scorers with 17 points. He also had five rebounds. 
</P>
