<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL / SIMI VALLEY TOURNAMENT; BLOUGH PUTS SIMI VALLEY HOME 
FREE AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES TEMMEL, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Anthony Tauriello scored 22 points and Dan Van Etten added 19 but it was Scott 
Blough who came up big again Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 After hitting the winning shot a day earlier to put Simi Valley High into the 
final, Blough sank two free throws with 25 seconds to play to preserve a 68-65 
victory over North Hollywood at Royal High, giving the Pioneers the 
championship of their own tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 And what was going through his mind as he stood on the line? 
</P>
<P>
 "Don't miss," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 After Blough's free throws, North Hollywood (3-1) still had a shot. But Arthur 
Lee's three-point attempt at the buzzer fell short. 
</P>
<P>
 "There was no doubt in my mind that I was going to make it," Lee said. "But as 
soon as it left my hand, I knew it would miss."  
</P>
<P>
 Lee finished with 25 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley (4-0) opened a 36-26 lead at halftime with a tenacious defense. 
</P>
<P>
 "We were really pleased with our defense," Simi Valley Coach Dean Bradshaw 
said. "It was a great team effort." 
</P>
<P>
 Royal 88, Palmdale 72 -- The Highlanders exploded for 26 points in the third 
quarter behind three three-pointers by Scott Hambly in the third-place game. 
</P>
