<HEADLINE>
<P>
GASTON 1 ROUND FROM ANOTHER WOMEN'S STATE AMATEUR TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Andrea Gaston of Chatsworth will attempt to become the first golfer since 1978 
to win consecutive Women's State Amateur championships when she meets Juli 
Christopher in the 18-hole final round today at the Golf Club at Quail Lodge in 
Carmel. 
</P>
<P>
 Golfing great Patty Sheehan won the tournament in 1977 and 1978. 
</P>
<P>
 Gaston, a member of the Porter Valley Country Club, defeated Eva Monisteri, 5 
and 4, Saturday to advance. 
</P>
<P>
 Christopher, the co-medalist, beat Diane Irvin, 4 and 3. Christopher was the 
runner-up in the 1992 Women's Amateur. 
</P>
<P>
 Gaston and Christopher have never played against each other, but played 
together during a practice round last summer. 
</P>
<P>
 "She's a longer-ball hitter," Gaston said. "The forecast is for rain (today) 
and with the wet conditions, she may have the advantage." 
</P>
<P>
 In the semifinal, Gaston took control early, going 3-up after seven holes then 
coasting to the victory in 14 holes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
