<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: WESTLAKE; WORKSHOPS ON SMALL BUSINESSES PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Developing Your Business Plan," the first of two December small-business 
workshops held Downtown by the Service Corps of Retired Executives, will be 
given Thursday at the Los Angeles Chamber of Commerce, 350 S. Bixel St. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop is 9:30 to 11 a.m. Registration at the door is $20. 
</P>
<P>
 The second workshop, "Starting and Operating Your Own Business," will be held 
Dec. 13 at the chamber offices for a $15 fee. 
</P>
<P>
 The service corps is made up of retired professionals who volunteer their time 
and experience to help others learn how to begin a business or improve it. 
</P>
<P>
 Several other workshops will be held throughout the month at the corps' 
Glendale office, including workshops on franchising, inventions, marketing and 
advertising. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (818) 552-3206 or 552-3207. 
</P>
</TEXT>
