<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; NEIGHBORHOOD PANEL APPLICANTS SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wanted: community-oriented Simi Valley residents interested in having a say in 
planning, development, traffic and environmental issues in their neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
 The city is accepting applications for its four neighborhood councils. 
</P>
<P>
 Board members meet on a monthly basis to review issues of interest to the 
community. 
</P>
<P>
 Neighborhood councils also sponsor volunteer events and participate in the 
Community Emergency Response Team Program. 
</P>
<P>
 Terms last two years, and applicants must be at least 18 years old. 
</P>
<P>
 The deadline for submitting applications is Jan. 6.  
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call Randi Joseph at 583-6756. SARA CATANIA 
