<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: VENTURA; METROLINK ON-TIME PERFORMANCE SLIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After a marked improvement in on-time performance, Metrolink train service 
slipped slightly in October, with 22% of the trains from Los Angeles to Ventura 
County arriving late. 
</P>
<P>
 Metrolink service to Ventura County has been plagued by delays, due in large 
part to aging tracks and a dispatching system that favors freight trains over 
commuter service, a Metrolink spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Transportation Commission Friday agreed to continue pressing for better 
on-time performance from the train service. 
</P>
<P>
 Late trains do not appear to be affecting ridership, which remained steady at 
about 1,500 passengers a day each way during October. 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, the commission is conducting a survey to determine where riders 
live. 
</P>
<P>
 Of 500 survey postcards placed on windshields in Metrolink parking lots in 
Simi Valley, Moorpark, Camarillo and Oxnard, 173 have been returned. 
</P>
<P>
 Of those, 38% are from Simi Valley, 15% apiece from Moorpark and Thousand 
Oaks, 13% from Camarillo, 10% from Oxnard, 5% from Ventura, 1% from Fillmore 
and 1% from Ojai. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
