<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATTACKS UNWARRANTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I have been an employee of The Worm Concern since April, 1994, and have lived 
in Simi Valley since 1986. 
</P>
<P>
 During this time I have never seen a rat (either dead or alive) at The Worm 
Concern and have not heard of any seen by other employees. 
</P>
<P>
 As for dust, since I started at The Worm Concern, they have instituted a fine 
misting watering system around the screen to control dust, and they have 
purchased a water truck to keep dust down around the property. I also 
understand that they have requested permission from the county to put a pad in 
for grinding and screening. This would also help control dust. 
</P>
<P>
 The odor complaints are very exaggerated and blown way out of proportion by 
the press. In fact, many of our customers remark how surprised they are to read 
in the papers about odors and some actually find the "earthy" smells pleasing. 
</P>
<P>
 There is an ongoing program at The Worm Concern to combat flies, and The Worm 
Concern is regularly monitored by the Moorpark Mosquito Abatement District for 
flies with favorable results. 
</P>
<P>
 As I observe the county strongly monitoring and coming down very hard on The 
Worm Concern (when it is performing a valuable service), I have also observed 
the neighbors getting away with similar violations. I also wonder why The Worm 
Concern is being so strongly attacked in the paper by people who have never 
been there. 
</P>
<P>
 The Worm Concern conducts free tours every Wednesday at 2 p.m., which are 
usually attended by Scouts, schools, environmentalists, home and professional 
recyclers, visitors from out of the area and many others. Call 520-1150 for an 
appointment. 
</P>
<P>
 JEANINE SATEL 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley 
</P>
