<HEADLINE>
<P>
39 HURT AS PHILADELPHIA TAXI PLOWS INTO CLUB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A taxi crashed through the glass facade of a crowded nightclub early Saturday, 
slid across the dance floor and struck the bar, injuring 39 people. 
</P>
<P>
 Some patrons were pinned to the floor when the taxi came to a stop in the 
private after-hours club during its grand opening. Others tipped the cab over 
to free those trapped underneath. Most of those hurt suffered scrapes and 
bruises; a few had fractures, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The cab driver was one of eight people admitted to city hospitals. He has not 
been charged, but the accident is being investigated, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
