<HEADLINE>
<P>
STYLE; THE MIDAS TOUCH; SIMPLE HOLIDAY GIFTS THAT GLITTER AND GLOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Barbara Thornburg 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Like objects in a Proust novel, this year's best gifts stir remembrances of 
holidays past, of colorful packages nestled under a tinsel-covered tree, warm 
candlelight filling a roomful of family and friends, evergreen wreaths scenting 
the air with fir and pine. Recapturing that old-fashioned spirit, these 
presents are elegant in their simplicity and, just as important, modest in 
price. Their rich golden patina is ideal for handsome gift-giving as well as 
festive home decorating. So be of good cheer: It is possible to enjoy the gilt 
without the guilt. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
