<P>
CITY ANALYSIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Aggregate crime in the county dropped by more than 5,500 incidents in 1993, 
compared to 1992. Most of that decline was recorded in two categories, burglary 
and larceny. Violent crimes declined by only about 100. By far the most 
striking difference occurred in Santa Ana, where incidents declined by around 
2,000. There were just over 600 more crimes in Huntington Beach, the city with 
the largest increase. 06,21,08,09,08,10,09 Total Forcible City crime Murder 
